WEBVTT

00:01.935 --> 00:04.703
(funky disco plays)
♪ My name is Cleveland Brown

00:04.705 --> 00:07.006
♪ And I am proud to be

00:07.008 --> 00:09.174
♪ Right back in my hometown

00:09.176 --> 00:12.111
♪ With my new family

00:12.113 --> 00:14.179
♪ There's old friends
and new friends ♪

00:14.181 --> 00:16.448
♪ And even a bear

00:16.450 --> 00:18.751
♪ Through good times
and bad times ♪

00:18.753 --> 00:20.252
♪ It's true love we share

00:20.254 --> 00:22.521
♪ And so I found a place

00:22.523 --> 00:24.857
♪ Where everyone will know

00:24.859 --> 00:27.026
♪ My happy mustached face

00:27.028 --> 00:29.261
♪ This is <i>The Cleveland Show.</i> ♪

00:29.263 --> 00:31.063
(chuckles)

00:33.533 --> 00:36.001
ANNOUNCER (on TV):
We now return to <i>Gay's Anatomy.</i>

00:36.003 --> 00:37.101
MAN:
There's his anus.

00:37.103 --> 00:40.939
Well, way too many channels
to just watch one.

00:40.941 --> 00:45.444
And now for my next trick,
I will cut a woman in half.

00:45.446 --> 00:48.113
You're just turning one problem
into two.

00:50.850 --> 00:52.951
What?!
I thought he was kidding.

00:52.953 --> 00:54.753
You can't... He's gonna kill
that woman!

00:54.755 --> 00:56.021
Help!

00:56.023 --> 00:57.589
Don't worry, Rallo, we're here.

00:57.591 --> 00:59.291
That guy on TV's
cutting...

00:59.293 --> 01:00.959
Why are you dressed
like that?

01:00.961 --> 01:03.162
We were playing <i>Raising Arizona.</i>

01:03.164 --> 01:04.596
Oh, I didn't see
that one.

01:04.598 --> 01:06.365
You've never seen
<i>Raising Arizona?!</i>

01:06.367 --> 01:08.033
You've gotta see it.

01:08.035 --> 01:09.368
I don't need to do anything.

01:09.370 --> 01:11.136
But that dude just cut
a woman in half.

01:11.138 --> 01:14.106
Oh, Rallo,
your innocence is endearing.

01:14.108 --> 01:15.374
That's just magic.

01:15.376 --> 01:16.842
What's that?

01:16.844 --> 01:19.144
Magic is the explanation
for the unexplainable.

01:19.146 --> 01:21.346
Like making a quarter vanish.

01:21.348 --> 01:23.182
Or pulling a rabbit
out of a hat.

01:23.184 --> 01:27.519
Or how Jack Black can utterly
disappear into every role.

01:27.521 --> 01:29.088
Magic.

01:31.091 --> 01:33.592
(chuckles) Me and Lester are
texting each other, Donna.

01:33.594 --> 01:36.962
Can you imagine him lying
in bed next to Kendra?

01:36.964 --> 01:39.932
They'd look like the
number ten. (chuckles)

01:39.934 --> 01:41.767
Oh... Mmm.

01:41.769 --> 01:43.469
I feel bad for Lester.

01:43.471 --> 01:45.604
Hey, guys, I got a
magic trick for you.

01:45.606 --> 01:47.206
Hey, hey, hey,
get out of here, Rallo.

01:47.208 --> 01:49.374
How do you know we weren't doing
something private?

01:49.376 --> 01:50.943
'Cause I don't hear
"Celebration"

01:50.945 --> 01:51.943
by Kool & the Gang.

01:51.945 --> 01:54.513
Now, think of a number
and then write it down,

01:54.515 --> 01:56.748
and only use this pen
and press really hard,

01:56.750 --> 01:59.685
and then rip it off
and don't let me see it.

02:02.021 --> 02:03.589
(scribbling)

02:03.591 --> 02:05.824
Okay. Was your number ten?

02:05.826 --> 02:07.526
Yeah. Poor Lester.

02:07.528 --> 02:09.761
Cute trick, Rallo.
Run along to bed.

02:09.763 --> 02:10.929
Hold on now.

02:10.931 --> 02:13.765
You haven't seen the incredible
floating cigarette.

02:13.767 --> 02:15.667
Rallo, where'd you get
that cigarette?

02:15.669 --> 02:18.437
Tobacco company rep was handing
'em out at the playground.

02:18.439 --> 02:20.305
Smart.
Now go back to bed.

02:20.307 --> 02:22.841
One more, one more.
Pick a card, any card.

02:22.843 --> 02:24.977
Jack of clubs.
Go away.

02:24.979 --> 02:26.178
Aw, man.

02:26.180 --> 02:27.379
(door closes)

02:27.381 --> 02:29.481
Why are you so hard
on that boy?

02:29.483 --> 02:30.949
Step-boy.

02:30.951 --> 02:33.185
You could've at least
let him have his moment.

02:33.187 --> 02:35.988
You could let
me have mine.

02:35.990 --> 02:39.324
(hums "Celebration")

02:39.326 --> 02:41.460
Uh-uh!

02:41.462 --> 02:43.495
Sorry, Kool. Sorry, Gang.

02:43.497 --> 02:44.630
Hopefully tomorrow night.

02:44.632 --> 02:45.631
(all groan)

02:45.633 --> 02:46.999
Damn!
Ain't that a bitch?

02:47.001 --> 02:49.434
Man, I was ready to play!

02:52.005 --> 02:53.805
AP calculus is wack

02:53.807 --> 02:55.974
wit dey derivative-ass
functions.

02:55.976 --> 02:58.777
You want to grow up to build
suspension bridges or not?

02:58.779 --> 03:00.479
Hey, Roberta,
there's a magic club

03:00.481 --> 03:02.447
over in Chester County,
and Mama can't drive me,

03:02.449 --> 03:05.117
so your dirtbag boyfriend's
gotta take me.

03:05.119 --> 03:06.251
Sorry. We're going to visit

03:06.253 --> 03:08.153
Federline's grandmother
in the hospital.

03:08.155 --> 03:11.089
Don't worry--
you won't see it.

03:12.192 --> 03:13.992
Cleveland!
You're my only hope.

03:13.994 --> 03:16.795
I need you to take me to
the magic club in Chester.

03:16.797 --> 03:21.500
Sorry, but I have my, uh,
fantasy women's billiards draft.

03:21.502 --> 03:23.001
Liar. That was last week.

03:23.003 --> 03:25.704
You got Ewa Mataya Laurance
in the first round.

03:25.706 --> 03:27.940
Hmm, The Striking Viking.

03:27.942 --> 03:29.041
Please?!
I'll do anything.

03:29.043 --> 03:30.442
Rallo, I really can't.

03:30.444 --> 03:32.144
You can just wait
in the car.

03:32.146 --> 03:33.345
I'm not doing it.

03:33.347 --> 03:34.379
Please!
No.

03:34.381 --> 03:35.514
Please!
No!

03:35.516 --> 03:37.082
Please, Dad.

03:38.418 --> 03:40.986
It's working.
The blended family is working.

03:40.988 --> 03:42.854
Rallo called me "Dad."

03:42.856 --> 03:44.156
Oh, Cleveland,
that's wonderful.

03:44.158 --> 03:46.491
I'm gonna mold that boy
into my own image.

03:46.493 --> 03:48.527
He'll be like a little me.

03:48.529 --> 03:50.128
A Cleveland Jr.,
if you will.

03:50.130 --> 03:52.598
You already have
a Cleveland Jr.

03:52.600 --> 03:54.132
Donna, I don't have time
for you to be right.

03:54.134 --> 03:55.434
I got to get dressed.

03:55.436 --> 03:58.036
I'm taking my boy
to the magic show.

03:58.038 --> 03:59.338
(voice breaking):
I just hope they have

03:59.340 --> 04:02.341
the pull-the-hanky-
from-the-sleeve act,

04:02.343 --> 04:05.777
'cause I'm gonna need
all 200 of 'em.

04:05.779 --> 04:07.779
(whimpers)

04:07.781 --> 04:09.581
You're gonna be fine.

04:09.583 --> 04:11.583
Lord knows you can't do
any worse than the last time

04:11.585 --> 04:13.986
Robert took Rallo
for the weekend.

04:13.988 --> 04:16.822
(cheering and whooping)

04:16.824 --> 04:18.490
(yelling)

04:18.492 --> 04:20.926
Put me down, you human garbage!

04:23.029 --> 04:25.097
(whimsical music plays)

04:34.340 --> 04:35.974
(à la Willy Wonka):
Hold your breath.

04:35.976 --> 04:39.044
Make a wish.

04:39.046 --> 04:40.779
Count to three.

04:40.781 --> 04:42.748
Now hold your breath again

04:42.750 --> 04:46.251
because I'm farting
and farting.

04:50.323 --> 04:51.423
Wow.

04:51.425 --> 04:53.058
See?

04:54.927 --> 04:56.828
Can you tell my fortune?

04:56.830 --> 04:58.030
Colon cancer.

04:58.032 --> 04:59.398
Dang.

05:03.002 --> 05:04.703
Wow.
Can I keep him?

05:04.705 --> 05:05.837
Of course you can.

05:05.839 --> 05:08.373
Anything you find in
your hat is yours.

05:08.375 --> 05:11.610
Ever since
<i>Stetson v. Oklahoma.</i>

05:11.612 --> 05:14.112
Cool, a Ferrari. Mine.

05:14.114 --> 05:16.648
(laughs, engine revs,
tires squeal)

05:16.650 --> 05:19.351
(screams, crashing sounds)

05:19.353 --> 05:21.920
Not my car.

05:21.922 --> 05:24.656
(siren wailing)

05:27.093 --> 05:28.994
(audience cheering)

05:31.331 --> 05:33.198
EMCEE:
And now ladies and gentlemen,

05:33.200 --> 05:37.002
our main attraction,
Magical Johnson!

05:37.004 --> 05:38.170
(audience cheering)

05:39.972 --> 05:42.007
(whispers):
That's my boy sitting on my lap.

05:42.009 --> 05:43.041
(whispers):
Good.

05:43.043 --> 05:45.110
Technically, my stepson,

05:45.112 --> 05:47.612
but he called me "Dad" today
for the first time.

05:47.614 --> 05:49.181
Congratulations.

05:49.183 --> 05:50.749
(sniffs deeply)

05:50.751 --> 05:53.919
His hair smells wonderful.
Take a whiff.

05:53.921 --> 05:55.253
I'm trying
to watch the show!

05:55.255 --> 05:57.255
Smell it!

05:57.257 --> 05:58.990
You're right.
It   <i>i</i>nice.

05:58.992 --> 06:00.158
Can I smell yours?

06:00.160 --> 06:02.127
You could, but I have to use

06:02.129 --> 06:06.031
special shampoo on account
of my "p-soriasis."

06:06.033 --> 06:07.165
(audience exclaims)

06:07.167 --> 06:08.600
Can we stay after the show

06:08.602 --> 06:11.002
to get Magical Johnson
to sign my program?

06:11.004 --> 06:14.206
We can stay here forever
as far as I'm concerned.

06:14.208 --> 06:16.108
Forever.

06:16.110 --> 06:17.476
(inhales deeply)

06:17.478 --> 06:18.844
Mmm...

06:19.812 --> 06:22.080
Oh, look at him--
all tuckered out

06:22.082 --> 06:25.484
from a magical day
with his wonderful dad.

06:25.486 --> 06:26.985
(groggily):
I'm not sleepy.

06:26.987 --> 06:29.187
I'm just gonna rest
my eyes...

06:29.189 --> 06:32.357
(snoring)

06:32.359 --> 06:36.027
♪ Nights in white satin

06:36.029 --> 06:40.098
♪ Never reaching the end

06:40.100 --> 06:43.001
♪ 'Cause I love you

06:43.003 --> 06:45.003
♪ Whoa-whoa-whoa

06:45.005 --> 06:49.040
♪ I love you.

06:49.042 --> 06:50.609
Hey, it's you!

06:50.611 --> 06:52.177
Magical Johnson is real!

06:52.179 --> 06:55.147
Rallo, wake up!

06:55.149 --> 06:57.949
What are you doing here?
The auditions are tomorrow.

06:57.951 --> 06:59.117
Auditions?

06:59.119 --> 07:01.153
Say, that's
a good-looking dummy.

07:01.155 --> 07:02.921
Who you calling a dummy,
dummy?

07:02.923 --> 07:04.022
That's not polite.

07:04.024 --> 07:05.791
Neither is beating
Daryl Hannah,

07:05.793 --> 07:07.926
but that didn't stop
Jackson Browne.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.694
(chuckles)
Okay, okay,
I've seen enough.

07:09.696 --> 07:11.596
You open
the show Sunday.

07:11.598 --> 07:12.798
Open the show?

07:12.800 --> 07:14.499
That's how we do it
with new acts.

07:14.501 --> 07:16.134
You do well, you move up.

07:16.136 --> 07:17.102
And you probably will.

07:17.104 --> 07:19.438
People love ventriloquists.

07:19.440 --> 07:21.606
I think there's
been a mistake...

07:21.608 --> 07:22.841
Is it a paying gig?

07:22.843 --> 07:25.710
You are paid quite handsomely
in ear coins.

07:25.712 --> 07:28.180
BOTH:
We'll make a waxy fortune!

07:28.182 --> 07:29.648
See you Sunday!

07:29.650 --> 07:31.316
Whoa.
You guys are good.

07:31.318 --> 07:33.752
But so am I.

07:35.288 --> 07:36.922
That's not what
I meant to do.

07:36.924 --> 07:38.890
Ta-tas!

07:44.130 --> 07:46.164
But, Donna, we're not
doing anything wrong.

07:46.166 --> 07:48.033
You'd be lying
to the audience.

07:48.035 --> 07:50.502
And teaching my son
to lie is not okay.

07:50.504 --> 07:52.971
You told him his
father was a war hero

07:52.973 --> 07:54.206
and then Santa Claus.

07:54.208 --> 07:56.174
It's okay to lie
to children.

07:56.176 --> 07:57.809
When I was raising Rallo
by myself,

07:57.811 --> 07:59.377
if I didn't make up
the bogeyman,

07:59.379 --> 08:00.645
I would've been so bored.

08:00.647 --> 08:02.681
But all magic is based on lying.

08:02.683 --> 08:05.116
David Copperfield doesn't
actually levitate

08:05.118 --> 08:06.918
or turn canes into doves.

08:06.920 --> 08:09.754
Although he did make
the Statue of Liberty disappear.

08:09.756 --> 08:12.123
That was real.
The one there now is fake.

08:12.125 --> 08:14.593
It's two inches shorter
and way hotter.

08:14.595 --> 08:19.498
You can read about it on
my blog: HTTP, equal sign,

08:19.500 --> 08:21.967
but with dots instead of dashes,

08:21.969 --> 08:24.870
leaning to the right line,
leaning to the right line,

08:24.872 --> 08:26.938
three W's, period,

08:26.940 --> 08:30.609
Statue of Duplicity--
all one word-- period,

08:30.611 --> 08:34.446
blogspot, period, C-O-M.

08:34.448 --> 08:36.615
I said no,
and that's final.

08:36.617 --> 08:37.916
Aw, dingleberries.

08:37.918 --> 08:41.286
Listen, Donna, I rarely
ask you for anything.

08:41.288 --> 08:42.921
You ask me
for things every day.

08:42.923 --> 08:44.155
Just this morning you asked

08:44.157 --> 08:46.525
if I would put on your uniform
and work your shift.

08:46.527 --> 08:47.659
And you didn't,

08:47.661 --> 08:49.995
so would you just do
this one thing for me?

08:49.997 --> 08:51.596
This is exactly the kind

08:51.598 --> 08:53.965
of father-son bonding
experience we need.

08:53.967 --> 08:56.134
We tried camping
in the backyard,

08:56.136 --> 08:57.969
but there was a scary cat.

08:57.971 --> 09:00.939
Okay, fine.
For you and Rallo.

09:00.941 --> 09:02.541
You can do your act.

09:02.543 --> 09:04.109
You won't regret this.

09:04.111 --> 09:05.176
I'm sure I will.

09:05.178 --> 09:06.811
Well, too bad.

09:06.813 --> 09:08.780
You agreed and I got
it all on tape.

09:08.782 --> 09:10.649
(muffled voice, heartbeat):
Okay, fine.

09:10.651 --> 09:11.917
(heartbeat slows)
For you and Rallo.

09:11.919 --> 09:13.919
(heartbeat increases)
You can do your act.

09:13.921 --> 09:15.987
Cleveland,
is that your heartbeat?

09:15.989 --> 09:18.023
Yeah, there's a
thumbtack in there.

09:18.025 --> 09:19.124
Mmm.

09:19.126 --> 09:21.860
You know, Dad, you two
are gonna need a manager.

09:21.862 --> 09:23.094
We should talk.

09:23.096 --> 09:24.696
You? A manager?

09:24.698 --> 09:26.498
What are
your qualifications?

09:26.500 --> 09:28.033
I can be very persuasive.

09:28.035 --> 09:29.501
Can't argue with that.

09:29.503 --> 09:31.269
You got it.

09:33.839 --> 09:36.107
♪ Hyum-hyum-ha...

09:36.109 --> 09:37.108
(clears throat)

09:37.110 --> 09:39.878
♪ Hyum-hyum-he...

09:39.880 --> 09:42.280
Babbling brook.

09:42.282 --> 09:44.015
Piper Perabo.

09:44.017 --> 09:46.418
Annal fissure.

09:46.420 --> 09:47.419
(clears throat)

09:47.421 --> 09:48.620
Vocals are warm.

09:48.622 --> 09:50.855
(chuckles)
You're my favorite client.

09:50.857 --> 09:53.191
How's my two favorite
clients doing?

09:53.193 --> 09:54.459
When are we on?

09:54.461 --> 09:55.794
All business.
I love it.

09:55.796 --> 09:56.995
You're up next.

09:56.997 --> 09:58.630
And if you see anyone
in the audience

09:58.632 --> 10:00.966
you want to "meet" after,
let me know.

10:00.968 --> 10:01.967
All right.

10:01.969 --> 10:03.268
Whoever's in
the front row.

10:03.270 --> 10:04.603
I want to find out how

10:04.605 --> 10:06.538
to get front row
tickets to things.

10:06.540 --> 10:10.108
Give a warm welcome to our next
act, John J. Porque

10:10.110 --> 10:13.311
and his recently adopted
inner-city son, Bean.

10:13.313 --> 10:16.615
That's right,
it's Porque and Bean!

10:16.617 --> 10:18.016
(applause and cheering)

10:18.018 --> 10:21.086
So, Bean, did you hear
what happened to the bee

10:21.088 --> 10:23.622
who went to the doctor
for sticky hair?

10:23.624 --> 10:25.323
No, Porque,
what happened?

10:25.325 --> 10:29.260
He told him
to stop using his honeycomb.

10:29.262 --> 10:31.863
(woman coughs)

10:33.132 --> 10:35.934
(clears throat)

10:35.936 --> 10:37.302
Word on the street is

10:37.304 --> 10:40.639
that Bazooka Joe's grandma
sewed him three socks.

10:40.641 --> 10:41.940
Why would she do that?

10:41.942 --> 10:46.411
Because she heard that over
the summer he grew another foot.

10:46.413 --> 10:47.946
MAN:
That's from gum.

10:47.948 --> 10:50.982
Ah, put me out
of my misery.

10:50.984 --> 10:53.585
Anyone want to toss a
brother in a wood chipper?

10:53.587 --> 10:54.819
(laughter)
Stick to the act.

10:54.821 --> 10:57.722
Stick to your diet,
you fat tub of crap.

10:59.191 --> 11:01.526
Now, <i>that's</i> clever.

11:01.528 --> 11:03.695
(audience laughing)

11:03.697 --> 11:07.332
Well, Bean, you got any other
problems with our act?

11:07.334 --> 11:10.535
Let's see, you got me dressed
up like black Chucky,

11:10.537 --> 11:12.137
you're doing
jokes so bad,

11:12.139 --> 11:14.539
even Carlos Mencia
wouldn't steal them,

11:14.541 --> 11:16.141
and according
to your breath,

11:16.143 --> 11:19.144
you just ate a tuna sandwich
with extra fart sauce.

11:19.146 --> 11:20.311
(laughter)

11:20.313 --> 11:21.746
They're so funny.

11:21.748 --> 11:23.748
You can't even see
his lips move.

11:23.750 --> 11:25.750
He's making
my lips move.

11:25.752 --> 11:28.019
(whispers):
This will get you backstage.

11:28.021 --> 11:29.154
Well, that's our time.

11:29.156 --> 11:31.156
Anything you want
to say before we go?

11:31.158 --> 11:32.157
Yeah. Help!

11:32.159 --> 11:33.825
AMBER Alert!

11:33.827 --> 11:35.160
(cheering)
That's our act!

11:35.162 --> 11:36.961
We're Porque and Bean!

11:36.963 --> 11:38.263
RALLO:
Good night!

11:41.300 --> 11:43.902
Now, that's some montage music.

11:45.104 --> 11:46.871
("Magic Stick" by Lil' Kim
featuring 50 Cent playing)

11:46.873 --> 11:48.306
♪ I got the magic stick

11:48.308 --> 11:50.608
♪ I know if I can hit it once

