♪ I'm in the telly
working up a sweat strokin' ♪

12:34.421 --> 12:36.488
♪ Tonight's the night
you could fall in love ♪

12:36.490 --> 12:39.124
♪ You could call your mama right
now, tell her you met a thug ♪

12:39.126 --> 12:40.925
♪ (bleep) pop a lot
'cause I can back it up... ♪

12:40.927 --> 12:42.961
Cut it! Cut the song!
(music stops)

12:42.963 --> 12:45.830
Hadn't really listened
to those lyrics before.

12:45.832 --> 12:49.934
Starting to think
the magic stick is <i>not</i> a wand.

12:49.936 --> 12:51.970
Did you hear that
crowd tonight?

12:51.972 --> 12:54.172
We tore this place
a new funny bone.

12:54.174 --> 12:57.108
I'm telling you, we killed,
like Michael Vick did

12:57.110 --> 12:58.777
to all those poor, innocent...

12:58.779 --> 13:01.946
NFL defenses.

13:01.948 --> 13:02.914
(laughs)

13:02.916 --> 13:04.983
He paid his dues, people,
let it go.

13:04.985 --> 13:07.318
That crowd
was eating me up.

13:07.320 --> 13:08.419
"Us" up.

13:08.421 --> 13:10.789
Please, Rallo,
you're just a prop.

13:10.791 --> 13:13.158
Nobody remembers
Oscar the Grouch.

13:13.160 --> 13:16.594
They remember his puppeteer,
Caroll Spinney.

13:16.596 --> 13:17.629
(knocking)

13:17.631 --> 13:18.763
One minute.

13:18.765 --> 13:20.198
(whispers):
Dummy mode.

13:23.702 --> 13:27.038
I'd like to introduce you
to Mr. Graham Kensington,

13:27.040 --> 13:30.809
the    <i>Chester Herald's</i>
<i>esteemed ventriloquist critic.</i>

13:30.811 --> 13:33.011
I've seen many a
man and his dummy

13:33.013 --> 13:35.013
tread the boards
in my time.

13:35.015 --> 13:36.948
Some good, some bad.

13:36.950 --> 13:38.483
But you...?

13:38.485 --> 13:41.119
You're no ventriloquist.

13:41.121 --> 13:42.120
I'm not?

13:42.122 --> 13:45.256
No.    <i>You'</i>an artiste!

13:45.258 --> 13:48.092
To think that one man,
one man,

13:48.094 --> 13:50.862
could do two
such disparate voices.

13:50.864 --> 13:52.130
It's a gift.

13:52.132 --> 13:56.301
You are single-handedly
redefining ventriloquism.

13:56.303 --> 13:57.969
I am only as great

13:57.971 --> 14:01.339
as the people who
notice how great I am.

14:03.943 --> 14:06.778
That act is all me.

14:06.780 --> 14:08.680
I feel so betrayed.

14:08.682 --> 14:11.149
This is worse than
what Judas did to Jesus.

14:12.117 --> 14:14.118
Man, I hope Tammy's here.

14:14.120 --> 14:15.987
Hey, can I see
that wine real quick?

14:15.989 --> 14:17.989
H-Hey! Hope you like red.

14:17.991 --> 14:20.024
Oh, thank you.

14:20.026 --> 14:22.961
You are so thoughtful,
Judas.

14:22.963 --> 14:24.863
Hi, Jesus.

14:24.865 --> 14:27.999
Strike two, Judas!

14:28.001 --> 14:30.935
So, what do you think
of my mustache?

14:30.937 --> 14:34.138
It's black and it stinks,
just like the rest of you.

14:34.140 --> 14:37.041
(laughs) Thank you. Thank you
for laughing at my joke.

14:37.043 --> 14:38.276
I do both voices.
Thank you.

14:38.278 --> 14:39.477
That's it!

14:39.479 --> 14:41.346
I'm sick of you
taking all the credit!

14:41.348 --> 14:43.081
All right, Bean.
That's enough.

14:43.083 --> 14:45.583
You don't want to go
back in your coffin.

14:45.585 --> 14:47.752
You're a no-talent,
credit-hogging hack!

14:47.754 --> 14:50.021
Bean, that's no way
to talk to your dad.

14:50.023 --> 14:52.023
Porque you. You're not my dad.

14:52.025 --> 14:54.926
I only called you that so you'd
take me to the magic show.

14:54.928 --> 14:56.661
No... you meant it.

14:56.663 --> 14:57.929
No, I played you.

14:57.931 --> 14:59.964
You're not my dad,
and you never will be.

14:59.966 --> 15:01.933
Getting a little too real.

15:01.935 --> 15:03.368
Yeah. And sexy.

15:03.370 --> 15:04.636
What?

15:04.638 --> 15:08.006
So then, it was all
just a... just a trick?

15:08.008 --> 15:08.973
That's right.

15:08.975 --> 15:12.377
(pained barking
seal sounds)

15:14.813 --> 15:18.349
Tell me that's not us.

15:19.985 --> 15:22.053
(sobbing)

15:28.627 --> 15:30.128
I'm sure Rallo didn't mean it.

15:30.130 --> 15:31.195
ROBERTA:
He meant it.

15:31.197 --> 15:34.966
See? He'll never
call me "Daddy" again.

15:34.968 --> 15:38.603
Hmm, hmm, soft face.

15:38.605 --> 15:40.805
Good God! Rallo, get in here!

15:40.807 --> 15:42.006
I don't want to see him.

15:42.008 --> 15:43.174
How do I look?

15:43.176 --> 15:45.510
Hey, Mama.
Hey, <i>not</i> Dad.

15:45.512 --> 15:46.978
(sobbing)
Gwah!

15:46.980 --> 15:48.279
Rallo, please tell him

15:48.281 --> 15:51.015
that what you said
was out of anger.

15:51.017 --> 15:54.252
You can see that I am
clearly not angry anymore.

15:54.254 --> 15:56.020
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

15:56.022 --> 15:59.590
You are not my father,
and you never will be.

16:00.759 --> 16:02.293
No! No!

16:02.295 --> 16:03.695
Tell me he didn't say it.

16:03.697 --> 16:04.862
Great news.

16:04.864 --> 16:07.865
I booked Porque and Bean
at The Orpheum Theater.

16:07.867 --> 16:09.100
No show!

16:09.102 --> 16:11.269
There's no porking way
I'm performing

16:11.271 --> 16:13.104
with that has-bean!

16:13.605 --> 16:15.039
That is it.

16:15.041 --> 16:16.941
I have had it up to here.

16:16.943 --> 16:19.077
You two are doing that show.

16:19.079 --> 16:20.278
And not because Junior

16:20.280 --> 16:21.913
put so much effort
into booking it.

16:21.915 --> 16:23.648
And not because the family

16:23.650 --> 16:25.450
could use a few extra bucks
this month.

16:25.452 --> 16:28.820
But because I refuse
to let ventriloquism

16:28.822 --> 16:30.188
tear this family apart.

16:30.190 --> 16:33.524
Not again. Never again.

16:33.526 --> 16:36.694
You two need to learn
to work together as a team.

16:36.696 --> 16:39.998
Not as master and puppet,
but as father and son.

16:40.000 --> 16:41.632
Uh-uh, push on, Mama.

16:41.634 --> 16:44.035
Do it or I'll tell everyone
at school

16:44.037 --> 16:46.004
about your Hello Kitty
cupcake oven.

16:46.006 --> 16:49.007
I just got that
to impress Asian girls.

16:49.009 --> 16:50.541
All right. I'll do it.

16:50.543 --> 16:52.610
Why do you care so much anyway?

16:52.612 --> 16:54.412
A mother's selflessness.

16:54.414 --> 16:58.583
How many blind mice do you
bitches wanna see tonight?!

16:58.585 --> 16:59.817
AUDIENCE:
Three!

16:59.819 --> 17:01.986
(playing "Three Blind Mice")

17:04.156 --> 17:07.125
Sorry, guys, I had to bundle
her act along with yours

17:07.127 --> 17:09.327
or she threatened to stop
making beef stroganoff.

17:09.329 --> 17:10.995
That's all right,
she jammin'.

17:10.997 --> 17:13.031
See how they run!

17:13.033 --> 17:16.034
And just so you know, I am
still not talking to you,

17:16.036 --> 17:17.535
that sentence not included.

17:17.537 --> 17:19.637
I have no problem
talking to you.

17:19.639 --> 17:22.173
Really? Good, because I thought
you weren't talking to me,

17:22.175 --> 17:23.975
so that's why I said
I wasn't talking to you,

17:23.977 --> 17:25.343
even though I wanted
to talk to you,

17:25.345 --> 17:27.111
but I was trying to
act all coolio and...

17:27.113 --> 17:28.746
But I am not talking
to them.

17:28.748 --> 17:29.947
Come again?

17:29.949 --> 17:32.116
You want a puppet, you got one.

17:32.118 --> 17:34.018
I'll move my mouth,
but that's it.

17:34.020 --> 17:36.954
Let's see how good
a ventriloquist you really are.

17:36.956 --> 17:38.122
(gulps)

17:38.124 --> 17:40.124
(applause and cheering)

17:40.126 --> 17:42.527
And now, for the act you've all

17:42.529 --> 17:45.463
inexplicably come to see...

17:45.465 --> 17:48.132
Porque and Bean!

17:48.134 --> 17:49.801
(cheering)

17:49.803 --> 17:54.439
I pray I haven't come all
this way for nothing, Graham.

17:54.441 --> 17:56.040
Trust me, Allister.

17:56.042 --> 17:57.775
You're in for
quite a treat.

17:57.777 --> 17:59.477
(whispers):
Julius, don't look.

17:59.479 --> 18:02.847
That's Allister Monkarsh
sitting behind us.

18:02.849 --> 18:04.148
The Karsh?!

18:05.451 --> 18:06.951
I said don't look.

18:06.953 --> 18:09.253
I hope to intern
for him someday.

18:09.255 --> 18:10.955
A critic's intern.

18:10.957 --> 18:12.790
What a nightmare.

18:12.792 --> 18:14.092
Good evening, folks.

18:14.094 --> 18:15.359
Say, "hello," Bean.

18:15.361 --> 18:16.928
Hello, Bean.

18:16.930 --> 18:19.263
Say, are you trying to do
an impression of me?

18:19.265 --> 18:20.631
Yes, sir.

18:20.633 --> 18:23.101
That's why I sound
very similar to you.

18:23.103 --> 18:24.435
That's pretty good.

18:24.437 --> 18:26.137
You do any other
impressions?

18:26.139 --> 18:27.338
No.

18:27.340 --> 18:29.040
Oh.

18:29.042 --> 18:32.977
So, Bean, anything you have
to say about my appearance?

18:32.979 --> 18:35.680
Yeah, you could stand
to lose a few pounds.

18:35.682 --> 18:37.014
For serious?

18:37.016 --> 18:38.349
No, I'm just joshing.

18:38.351 --> 18:41.652
The only thing you need
to lose is your humility.

18:41.654 --> 18:44.055
(audience booing)

18:45.424 --> 18:47.024
MAN:
I missed my wife's funeral
for this?

18:47.026 --> 18:48.159
MAN 2:
This is a funeral.

18:48.161 --> 18:49.827
MAN 1 (laughs):
Oh, you're bad.

18:49.829 --> 18:51.896
(booing continues)

18:56.835 --> 18:59.103
(clears throat)

18:59.105 --> 19:01.806
Ladies and gentleman,
I have a confession.

19:01.808 --> 19:03.608
You have been lied to.

19:03.610 --> 19:04.909
Don't do this.

19:04.911 --> 19:06.310
No, I have to.

19:06.312 --> 19:09.914
There's only one dummy up here
tonight and that's me.

19:09.916 --> 19:13.184
When you called me "Dad,"
it changed everything.

19:13.186 --> 19:16.954
Every fight we ever had,
every insult you ever made,

19:16.956 --> 19:21.092
every ball of mine you ever
punched was all wiped away.

19:21.094 --> 19:23.961
Because from the moment
I became your dad,

19:23.963 --> 19:28.432
it's become the only thing
that I want to be.

19:28.434 --> 19:30.935
But I already have a dad.

19:30.937 --> 19:32.003
I know that.

19:32.005 --> 19:34.272
But who says
you can't have two?

19:34.274 --> 19:35.473
MAN:
God.

19:35.475 --> 19:38.943
Folks, this boy is why
you're here tonight.

19:38.945 --> 19:42.980
He's been the brains behind
this operation since day one.

19:42.982 --> 19:44.415
He's the talent.

19:44.417 --> 19:45.816
I'm the dummy.

19:45.818 --> 19:49.086
You already used that metaphor,
fat face.

19:49.088 --> 19:51.289
I mean, fat Dad.

19:51.291 --> 19:55.459
Oh, oh, oh, oh,
my boy is back.

19:55.461 --> 19:56.928
Oh, oh, oh.

19:56.930 --> 19:59.931
(sniffing)
Mmm... mmm...

19:59.933 --> 20:02.099
(sniffs)
Mmm...

20:02.101 --> 20:04.202
(cheering)

20:05.137 --> 20:07.772
Hazel, get this down
for the evening edition.

20:07.774 --> 20:11.242
"Even while sobbing,
his lips never moved,

20:11.244 --> 20:15.112
but tongues will be wagging
about Porque and Bean!"

20:15.114 --> 20:18.149
And, uh... yes, that's it.

20:18.151 --> 20:19.951
That's the end of the article.

20:19.953 --> 20:22.420
Junior, rent a bus.

20:22.422 --> 20:24.488
Because this show's
going to Carnegie Hall.

20:24.490 --> 20:25.823
You hear that, Mama?

20:25.825 --> 20:28.092
I'm gonna play
Carnegie Hall.

20:28.094 --> 20:31.028
So screw you, Mama!

20:31.030 --> 20:32.797
(sobbing)

20:32.799 --> 20:35.099
I miss you.

20:36.101 --> 20:38.736
Go ahead.

20:39.705 --> 20:42.206
(audience gasping)

20:43.342 --> 20:45.076
The dummy's come alive!

20:45.078 --> 20:47.345
He'll kill us all!

20:47.347 --> 20:50.715
(panicked screaming)
